{"parse":{"title":"Ann Ferguson","pageid":38861203,"revid":824205846,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For those of the same or a similar name, see <a href=\"/wiki/Anne_Ferguson_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Anne Ferguson (disambiguation)\">Anne Ferguson (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Ann Ferguson</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span style=\"display:none\"> (<span class=\"bday\">1938-03-06</span>) </span>6 March 1938<span class=\"noprint ForceAgeToShow\"> (age&#160;80)</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td class=\"org\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Amherst\" title=\"University of Massachusetts Amherst\">University of Massachusetts Amherst</a></td></tr><tr class=\"note\"><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Main interests</div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Feminist_theory\" title=\"Feminist theory\">Feminist theory</a></td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Ann Ferguson</b> (born 6 March 1938),<sup id=\"cite_ref-DOB_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DOB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is an American <a href=\"/wiki/Philosopher\" title=\"Philosopher\">philosopher</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Professor_Emerita\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Professor Emerita\">Professor Emerita</a> of Philosophy and Women's Studies at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Amherst\" title=\"University of Massachusetts Amherst\">University of Massachusetts Amherst</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> She served as Amherst's director of women\u2019s studies from 1995 to 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> She is known for her work on <a href=\"/wiki/Feminist_theory\" title=\"Feminist theory\">feminist theory</a>.\n</p><p>She established the Ann Ferguson Women and Gender Studies Scholarship in 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_books\">Selected books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ann_Ferguson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Ferguson, Ann (1989). <i>Blood at the root: motherhood, sexuality and male dominance</i>. London: Pandora. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780044404453\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780044404453\">9780044404453</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Blood+at+the+root%3A+motherhood%2C+sexuality+and+male+dominance&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Pandora&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.isbn=9780044404453&amp;rft.aulast=Ferguson&amp;rft.aufirst=Ann&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnn+Ferguson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Ferguson, Ann (1991). <i>Sexual democracy: women, oppression, and revolution</i>. Boulder, Colorado: Westview Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780813307473\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780813307473\">9780813307473</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Sexual+democracy%3A+women%2C+oppression%2C+and+revolution&amp;rft.place=Boulder%2C+Colorado&amp;rft.pub=Westview+Press&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=9780813307473&amp;rft.aulast=Ferguson&amp;rft.aufirst=Ann&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnn+Ferguson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Ferguson, Ann; Bar On, Bat-Ami (1998). <i>Daring to be good: essays in feminist ethico-politics</i>. New York: Routledge. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415915540\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415915540\">9780415915540</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Daring+to+be+good%3A+essays+in+feminist+ethico-politics&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=9780415915540&amp;rft.aulast=Ferguson&amp;rft.aufirst=Ann&amp;rft.au=Bar+On%2C+Bat-Ami&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnn+Ferguson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Ferguson, Ann; Nagel, Mechthild (2009). <i>Dancing with Iris the philosophy of Iris Marion Young</i>. Oxford New York: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195389111\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780195389111\">9780195389111</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dancing+with+Iris+the+philosophy+of+Iris+Marion+Young&amp;rft.place=Oxford+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=9780195389111&amp;rft.aulast=Ferguson&amp;rft.aufirst=Ann&amp;rft.au=Nagel%2C+Mechthild&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnn+Ferguson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Ferguson, Ann; <a href=\"/wiki/Anna_G._J%C3%B3nasd%C3%B3tt%C3%ADr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anna G. J\u00f3nasd\u00f3tt\u00edr\">J\u00f3nasd\u00f3ttir, Anna G</a> (2014). <i>Love: a question for feminism in the twenty-first century</i>. New York: Routledge Advances in Feminist Studies and Intersectionality. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415704298\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415704298\">9780415704298</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Love%3A+a+question+for+feminism+in+the+twenty-first+century&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Routledge+Advances+in+Feminist+Studies+and+Intersectionality&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=9780415704298&amp;rft.aulast=Ferguson&amp;rft.aufirst=Ann&amp;rft.au=J%C3%B3nasd%C3%B3ttir%2C+Anna+G&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnn+Ferguson\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ann_Ferguson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-DOB-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-DOB_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nr8901